  {# Design Philosophy                            #}
  {# ============================================ #}

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 border-b-3 border-primary-500 pb-2 mb-6">Design Philosophy</h2>
    <div class="prose prose-lg">
      <p>This site is generated from two inputs: a PDF document (content) and a reference URL (design). The design system merges both streams into a cohesive visual identity.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Content-first:</strong> Design serves the content, not the other way around.</li>
        <li><strong>Accessible by default:</strong> WCAG 2.1 AA minimum. Underlined links, visible focus states, sufficient contrast.</li>
        <li><strong>Zero client-side JavaScript:</strong> Only a hamburger menu toggle. Everything else is HTML + CSS.</li>
        <li><strong>System fonts for body:</strong> Zero load cost, excellent screen readability.</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive from mobile up:</strong> Every section works at 320px before scaling to desktop.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

