  <section class="mb-16" id="accessibility">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 border-b-3 border-primary-500 pb-2 mb-6">Accessibility</h2>
    <div class="prose prose-lg">
      <p>Target: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance on all pages.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Skip link:</strong> Hidden until focused, jumps to <code>#main</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Links:</strong> Permanently underlined (WCAG 1.4.1 — not just on hover).</li>
        <li><strong>Focus states:</strong> Visible on all interactive elements.</li>
        <li><strong>Color contrast:</strong> All text-on-background combinations meet AA ratios.</li>
        <li><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>aria-current="page"</code> on active items, <code>aria-expanded</code> on hamburger.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>The Grayscale Test</h3>
      <p>View the site with color removed and ask: "Can I still tell what's interactive?" Links should be identifiable by their underline, buttons by their shape, and focus states by their outline — not just by color.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

